result.description:
This is a report that:
- Sets out the (different) ways in which societal engagement in the context of RRI is currently conceived of and conceptualized;
- Points out whether/how these conceptions of societal engagement relate to those of already existing approaches on shaping of science, technology and innovation, and to what extent RRI notions introduce novel perspectives of societal engagement with R&I;
- Discusses presuppositions and implications for implementing societal engagement as conceived of by RRI notions, particularly in terms of providing opportunities or challenges in relation to current practice of societal engagement with RRI in Europe.
